OL,3,CWomen have 'traumatic experience' at
OL,4,Cmaternity services, review reveals
OL,6,FThe review did find some evidence of
OL,7,Fimprovements, with staffing levels
OL,8,Fimproving since 2024 and a reduction
OL,9,Fin perinatal mortality since 2023.
OL,11,FThe Chair of the Review, Dr. Denise
OL,12,FChaffer, said whilst improvements have
OL,13,Fbeen made in the past few years,
OL,14,Fsignificant work still needs to be
OL,15,Fdone.
